LeBron James isn't ready to let his two sons strap on shoulder pads and a helmet just yet.

The NBA superstar doesn't want his boys, LeBron Jr. and Bryce, to play organized football because of safety concerns. He hasn't ruled them out playing the sport in the future, but for now he's insisting they stay off the field.

'We don't want them to play in our household right now until they understand how physical and how body demanding the game is,' James said following practice on Thursday. 

'Then they can have their choice in high school, we'll talk over it. But right now there's no need for it. There's enough sports they can play. They play basketball, they play soccer, they play everything else but football and hockey.'

