James told ESPN.com last week while the Cavaliers were in Denver that that he didn't want his sons playing football because of the sport's dangers. 

'Only basketball, baseball and soccer are allowed in my house,' James said

He's made similar comments in the past to the Associated Press.

'It's a safety thing,' he said Thursday. 

'As a parent you protect your kids as much as possible. I don't think I'm the only one that's not allowing his kids to play football, it's just that I'm LeBron James and it gets put in the headlines for no reason.'

James often refers to himself as a football player when talking about making physical plays. He's also a big football fan, and closely follows the Dallas Cowboys, Browns and Ohio State.

